Dear friends and family,

We are thrilled to announce the arrival of our son, Ellington Rex Balbuena! He was born on Friday, February 24th, 2023 and weighed 6 pounds and 10 ounces and 19 inches long. Both baby and mom are doing great, and we couldn't be happier to welcome our newest family member into the world.

I want to take a moment to express my deepest gratitude to my wife Amanda for her strength and perseverance during her pregnancy. She underwent major surgery, battled gestational diabetes, dealt with carpal tunnel in both hands, random aches, pains and kept her blood pressure in check to ensure a healthy pregnancy and safe delivery. We are in awe of her courage and resilience, and we can't thank her enough for bringing our beautiful son into this world.

We also want to thank our family and friends for their love and support throughout this journey. Your kind words, prayers, and encouragement have meant the world to us, and we are grateful to have you in our lives.

We can't wait for you all to meet Ellington and watch him grow and thrive. He is already filling our hearts with love and joy, and we know he will bring happiness to all those who meet him.

With love and gratitude,
Rex and Amanda

From Heartbeat to Heartfull.. Happy 1 Week Ellington! I made this beat before he was born sampling his heartbeat at 84bpm. It’s called Blueberry Heartbeat as we called him Blueberry before he was born because that’s what his size was when we found out we were expecting. It’s on Spotify under DJ Wrex.
